@startuml
title BP-02 - User Login and Tenant Workspace Selection

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  DiamondBackgroundColor White
  DiamondBorderColor Black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}

|User|
start
:Open login page;
:Submit email and password;

|Platform|
:Find user by email;
if (User exists?) then (Yes)
  :Verify password hash;
else (No)
  :Return invalid credential error;
  stop
endif

if (Password valid?) then (Yes)
  :Load active UserTenantRole records;
else (No)
  :Return invalid credential error;
  stop
endif

if (Access records found?) then (Yes)
  :Build one login response per tenant role;
else (No)
  :Return access not configured error;
  stop
endif

if (Role is STUDENT?) then (Yes)
  :Resolve StudentID for token claim;
else (No)
  :Leave StudentID empty;
endif

:Generate JWT containing UserID, TenantID, RoleCode and optional StudentID;
:Return available workspaces with tokens;

|User|
:Choose tenant workspace and role;
:Use selected token for protected APIs;
stop

note right
Technical rules:
- TenantID must come from UserTenantRole.
- Client must not choose arbitrary TenantID.
- Each token represents exactly one tenant role context.
end note
@enduml
